They are often forced to migrate to other regions in search for grazing land and food. The decomposing remains of livestock that dot vast stretches of land bear witness to the extent of the drought. They leave their wives and children back home to wait the government's food aid. Abdulkerim Aden Hassen is a government official involved in distributing food aid at Gerbi Kebele says they are giving food to 800 families so far. Some of the displaced livestock keepers have been received by villagers in the less affected zone of Fafen. --ChannelAfrica--